It wasn't a body in general. Kind of like an all purpose storage device. Think of it like this:

Putting an Asgard brain into a different host is like trying to put and old style RS-232 connection into a serial port. They both do the same thing but expected connections are in different places.

Putting a consciousness into a computer is like putting an IDE bus onto a jumper block (not in any way suggesting functionality simply size wise). There are far less connections and less chance of incompatibility. All of those sockets on the IDE cable for controlling motor skills have no partners and therefore no incorrect connections.
